rComments: He is a great teacher and was able to make a really condensed and heavy material extremely clearly in an extremely short period of time.

Coulombe's lectures are the best lectures I've experienced, he's engaging, concise, and great at conveying the subject matter. He makes sure to clearly outline what concepts you need to understand for his exam, and he's always available if you have any questions.

I would highly recommend this prof, especially for any French Immersion students! Great lectures with clear content, and engaging enough that it's not hard to pay attention and learn. That's not to say it's a super easy course; it still requires a considerable amount of work, but if you do it, you're golden. Again, absolutely outstanding prof.
Serge est un bon professeur et il explique très bien les concepts. Il n'y a pas de surprises sur les examens; il explique bien d'avance ce qui sera présent.

Didn't like the teaching  but the class is relatively easy. Read your textbook and do couple exercises and you should be fine. Watch out for true or false on exams, he tries to trick you with double negations

Prof is amazing. His lectures, although they can get a bit repetitive at times, are useful and interesting. Midterms and exam are fair as long as you put in the work and study. Great prof to have for French Immersion students -- easy to understand. 10/10 would recommend.

Monsieur Coulombe est un excellent professeur qui explique très bien son cours, il se refaire au livre pour ce qui est des exemples mais l'explique à sa façon ce qui aide beaucoup à la compréhension. Ses exams sont assez long mais très facile si tu as suivis en classe ou lu au moins le livre. Bravo à ce professeur!

He does not care about his students success. He writes his multiple choices to purposely trick you into choosing the wrong answer. If you do not like multiple choices, dont take his class. If you do like multiple choices, dont take his class either.

Great prof, lectures were always very engaging.  No course notes/slides/textbook, just handwritten notes on the blackboard to accompany oral lectures. Very good at conveying material, and exams were based on lectures and blackboard notes only.
I found his lectures confusing and relied on the textbook. There is minimal work involved, but beware of the multiple choice exams, they are not as easy as they sound.

Really good teacher. Go to class because he gives examples that are on the tests. Lectures are long but he makes them somewhat interesting. You can tell that he knows what he's talking about and he's there for you if you need help (email).

I loved economics. I didn't use the textbook because, for me, the powerpoint and notes in class were enough. I recommend you go to class cuz he gives really great examples in class and very pertinent notes. He gives lots of answer for the mid term and final so go. He is also really passionate about the material he teaches so the lectures are ok.
Really easy tests, if you go to class or read the book, you'll get a good grade.

The prof does not have powerpoint nor follows the textbook. All notes on written in class so if you skip class you are screwed. Hilarious prof connects economics theories and current events. Very knowledgeable although not the most organized or clear notes.

Serge is very entertaining and knowledgeable man! He gives good examples and makes microeconomics much funner than it is. He is also clear about what needs to be studied/understood for exams and his exams reflect what you learn very well. I'd recommend him to anyone
Terrible. Boring. I fall asleep every class. But he's very knowledgeable

He's average. All i did was pay attention to the lectures and didn't have to do much readings. But on the other hand, my friend who didn't go to class just read all the chapters and got the same grade as me so basically you don't have to go to class, but it'll help for the exemples he gives in class.
Put in the work and you'll do great

Very good professor. He is able to explain properly what needs to be learned and gives good exemples. II found his course interesting and he answers well to questions. To get good grades, read the book and the do the excercises in the book. He is very clear on how the exams will be and what he is expecting.

Has dynamic teaching. I was actually kept interested throughout the lectures. However, make sure to not miss a class because the textbook isn't enough to fully understand the subject as he often goes farther and explain the concepts.

Probably the smartest prof I've had since I'm in the university. His lectures are extremely interesting but he expects the students to keep up. Work hard and you will do well. Long assignments but very interesting.
Bon prof! Très dynamique!
He is a great prof who makes class fun.  He speaks clearly and sets out clear expectations of students.  Exams are very fair.  Great prof for students in immersion.

He is better than the book (though you are better served by reading the textbook alongside his notes). He knows his material and is clearly passionate about it. He maintains the bridge between the material and the real world, and expects you, especially in exams, to understand the real world applications of theories and models. FUN CLASS!
Great prof. Gives good explanations, but the only way you'll do well is if you read the textbook.

Très bon prof! Donne d'excellentes explications! Il sait de quoi il parle, et si jamais tu ne comprends pas quelque chose, le livre est très utile! Ses examens peuvent être un peu difficile, mais si tu t'y prépares bien, aucun problème! :)
EXCELLENT! best teacher ever!! il explique vrm bien! jle conseil a tout le monde! ses examens sont super facile! j'ai eu A+ dans son cours! J'ai adoré venir a ses cours!
Energetic and doesn't give boring lectures.

Ce prof est très dynamique, même s'il a enseigné la microéconomie quand son expertise est la macroéconomie. Il faisait beaucoup d'erreurs dans ses explications alors le manuel est assez important d'avoir. Ces examens sont relativement faciles (80% choix multiples et 20% questions à court développement).

Great professor.  He explains the material very effectively.  He answers questions in class, and is very passionate about what he teaches. Sadly this course is about Keynes' theories, and the Prof Loves Paul Krugman (leftist).  But whether or not you agree with the theories, they are explained well.  Humor in class is also great.
Very smart guy, knows his stuff. Assignments are hard and exams are tough, but marked fairly.
this guy is the man... great proff

Great prof, makes things clear, and used course content in relation to modern economic events and circumstances particularly affecting the American economy. A very interesting course if you?re interested in what?s happening in the world since the recession.

thème choisi-dévellopement et croissance économique: Il est très intéressant et comprend bien la matière.  Il faut savoir pratiquement tout dans le manuel pour les intras.  Les questions pratiques dans le manuel aident bcp pour les intras.  J'ai bcp appris dans son cours : )
He is not helpful. Expects us to know most of the stuff before hand.
L'enthousiasme à l'état brut. Toujours prêt à aider les étudiants, très intéressant à entendre. Peut-être moins clair en anglais, mais en français c'est super.
No Comments
No Comments
He's not that bad

keeps our interests
